At 11:22 AM 7/31/96, sethf@mit.edu wrote:
&gt;the only power in society that matters is government power
&gt;Another very common Libertarian-definition tick
&gt;for some reason they *immediately* jump to rhetoric
&gt;business is the fundamental basis of Libertarian theories
&gt;there's an extremely deep anxiety generated
&gt;an almost hysterical flaming to stop thinking about them
&gt;*by definition* business actions can't be wrong in any way

Seth, this list is not really the appropriate place for trolls or
generalized libertarian baiting. I for one would appreciate it if you'd
knock it off in this forum; distortions, insults, and amateur
psychoanalysis are not only not helpful, they're actively harmful in
sidetracking discussion and creating rifts and ugly feelings toward one
another.

If you do believe in freedom of expression as a basic principle and
something that's worth having in itself - something I am beginning to doubt
after having read some of your writings over the last months - then please
do not undermine efforts to secure it by flamebaiting on this list. Thank
you.

--
The Internet interprets the US Congress as system damage
and routes around it.   - with apologies to John Gilmore


</pre>

