	Is it the place for trolls and generalized Libertarian ranting?

&gt; I for one would appreciate it if you'd knock it off in this forum; 

	Similarly, I'd appreciate it if I didn't have to hear the
"Libertarian" view of the proper use of the word censorship over and over
again. But given that it's inevitable that that happens, and I think
it's distracting and politically annoying, what do you suggest I do?
Keep silent about it?

&gt; distortions, insults, and amateur psychoanalysis are not only not
&gt; helpful, they're actively harmful in sidetracking discussion and
&gt; creating rifts and ugly feelings toward one another.

	I think the rifts and ugly feelings are created initially by the
harsh criticism of the person holding a non-Libertarian view. I think if
you'll examine the record of this thread, you'll see that's the history.

&gt;If you do believe in freedom of expression as a basic principle and
&gt;something that's worth having in itself - something I am beginning to doubt
&gt;after having read some of your writings over the last months - then please

	??? I cannot imagine how you can say this. Let's take it to e-mail.

&gt;do not undermine efforts to secure it by flamebaiting on this list.
&gt;Thank you.

	To be frank, I think very little of Libertarianism as a
political philosophy.  But more importantly, and somewhat relevant to
this list, I've come to believe that the habits of thought it engenders
are downright harmful, that they tend to keep people from thinking
effectively about the real world - which is a very complicated mix of
government, business, social customs, and so on, all interacting with
each other. In fact, I just wrote a long article where these very points
took up much of the space. Check out, at the Ethical Spectacle webzine,
(http://www.spectacle.org/)
   Linkname: Internet Blocking Programs and Privatized Censorship
        URL: http://www.spectacle.org/896/finkel.html

	Thus, I very much want to argue against such a worldview. I
don't view this as "flamebaiting", but as "political argument" (although
I am rough at times, but this is somewhat in anticipation of stock stuff
like being called a thief and a Stalinist). Given this background, what
are your suggestions as to what should be done?

================
Seth Finkelstein
sethf@mit.edu

