<hr>
    <h1>[3407] <a href="dl?thread=Have+you+heard?&after=3407">Have you heard?</a></h1>
    <h2><i>Dara Sales &lt;pinky@pond.com&gt;</i></h2>
    <pre>
<b>Subject</b>: Have you heard?
<b>To</b>: fight-censorship@vorlon.mit.edu
<b>From</b>: Dara Sales &lt;pinky@pond.com&gt;
<b>Date</b>: Thu, 8 Aug 1996 17:10:48 -0400
<b>Message-id</b>: &lt;199608082110.RAA04844@wanda.phl.pond.com&gt;

Get this one.  I just heard it on the afternoon news.  Two young boys were
seriously burned after a failed attempt at making napalm on their kitchen
stove.  Sounds like the normal fun activities of bored youth on summer break
right?  But hey - where did they get the recipe?  From the Anarchists
Cookbook in the library?  No - they got it from -- GASP -- the Anarchists
Cookbook on the Internet.  Authorities (and a myriad of censor happy wackos
-- most of which heard about the story on their way to California for some
sort of convention) are deciding whether or not to press charges.  See -
just one more example of how the Internet rots your mind, corrupts the
morals of young souls and causes madness and mayhem.

pinky
The Legal Pad
http://legal-pad.com

</pre>

