At 12:26 PM 8/8/96, Jason Stokes wrote:
&gt;&gt;Perhaps I have little legal recourse since GeoCities was sponsoring the disk
&gt;&gt;space (which I credited with their logo and a link back to them). But I do
&gt;&gt;sense great deception on their part with a theme-based neighborhood like
&gt;&gt;"West Hollywood", which in the real world is a locale known for its freedom
&gt;&gt;of expression in art and lifestyles.
&gt;
&gt;As a free service, Geocities has the right to determine which pages it
&gt;decides to sponsor.  This is not a good incident to espouse free speech
