<title>Technical Info</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="ut09img0.gif">
<p><font size=6><b><u>Technical Info</u></b></font> </p>
<p>Although we try to simplify the Somatidian Orthobiology as much as possible, some technical 
details are necessary for therapists and anyone interested to deepen knowledge in this field. </p>
<hr>
<p><a href="ti03imga.htm"><img src="ti03img0.gif" align=left hspace=5 width=75 height=70></a><font size=5><b>Mounting the condenser</b></font></p>
<blockquote>
<p>This section describes how to mount the Naessens' condenser</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><a href="ti04imga.htm"><img src="ti04img0.gif" align=left hspace=5 width=75 height=67></a><font size=5><b>Centering the condenser</b></font></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Prior to its use, the condenser must be centered. This section describes the 
step by step method for centering the condenser</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><a href="ti05imga.htm"><img src="ti05img0.gif" align=left hspace=5 width=75 height=123></a><font size=5><b>714X - Handbook</b></font></p>
<blockquote>
<p>714X - A Highly promising Non-Toxic Treatment for Cancer and Other 
Immune Deficiencies. This document explains the 714X Treatment, how it 
interacts with the immune system and technical information that one might 
need to know.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><a href="ti06imga.htm"><img src="ti06img0.gif" align=left hspace=5 width=75 height=66></a><font size=5><b>714X - Injection Technique</b></font></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The injection of 714X is not painful when done properly. In this section, 
specific frames from the video tape &quot;The Injection Technique&quot; have been digitized 
to explain the step by step injection technique.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><a href="ti02imga.htm"><img src="ut07img0.gif" align=left hspace=5 width=133 height=78></a><font size=5><b>Legal use of the 714X in Canada</b></font></p>
