<html>

<head>
<title>The Nassens' Condenser</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="ut02img0.jpg" link="#FF0000" vlink="#FF0000">
<h1><font color="#FFFF00">The Naessens' Condenser</font></h1>
<p><font color="#FFFF00"><img src="pr05lnk0.gif" align=right border=1 hspace=10 width=150 height=148></font></p>
<p><font color="#00FFFF"><font size=4>More than 40 years ago, Gaston Naessens invented the 
Somatoscope, a microscope capable of reaching 30,000X 
magnification with a 15nm resolution on living blood samples. 
Since then, Mr. Naessens developed a condenser permitting 
Ultramicroscopy. The condenser is adaptable to most 
microscopes, and available to all Health Care Professionals. The Ultramicroscope 
makes it possible to observe processes in freshly extracted blood and to view its 
subcellular components. Gaston Naessens hypothesizes that all living beings, 
animal and vegetable, possess life by virtue of microscopic dense particles which 
he calls &quot;Somatids&quot;. His unique approach to study morphological correlates of 
health from blood samples (Cancer, MS, Progressive Rheumatoid Arthritis...) 
relies on using his Somatoscope and Ultramicroscope to view the abnormal </font></font><a href="ti05imga.htm#Cycle"><font color="#00FFFF"><font size=4>cycle 
of the Somatids</font></font></a><font color="#00FFFF"><font size=4> in the blood. (Orthodox Medicine has no live blood test for 
cancer.) Studies in standardizing this blood test are presently in progress. 
Eventually, the results of these studies may lead to the elaboration of a blood test 
for diagnostic purposes and meet the approval requirements of the Canadian 
Medical Authorities. </font></font></p>
</body>

</html>
