<title>Legal use of the 714X in Canada</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="ut13img0.gif" text="#FFFF00">
<p><img src="ut07img0.gif" align=bottom width=133 height=78> <font color="#FFFFFF"><font size=5><b>Legal use of the 714X in Canada</b></font></font><font size=5><b> </b></font></p>
<p><b><i>The use of 714X (Trimethylbicyclonitraminoheptane Cl)</i></b> <b><i>is authorized in Canada by the</i></b> 
<b><i>Health Protection Branch (H.P.B.), Ottawa,</i></b> <b><i>in conformity with article C.08.010</i></b> <b><i>of the 
Drug and Food Law (Emergency Drug Section)</i></b> </p>
<p><b><i>Any Canadian doctor can obtain the 714X by requesting the</i></b> <b><i>Health Protection Branch 
(H.P.B.)</i></b> <b><i>for an authorization to use this product.</i></b> </p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Telephone............: (613) 941-2108</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">After work hours..: (613) 941-3061</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFFFF">Fax.......................: (613) 941-3194</font></p>
<p><blink>Emergency Drug Section</blink></p>
