<head>
<title>Mounting the Naessens' Condenser</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="ut10img0.gif">
<h1>Mounting the Naessens' Condenser</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p align=center><img src="ti09imga.gif" align=bottom width=249 height=117></p>
<hr>
<p><img src="ti10img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=141 height=150><font size=5>Unscrew de ring of the condensor body until it 
moves freely.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p align=left><img src="ti11img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=149 height=150></p>
<p align=left><img src="ti12img0.gif" align=bottom border=2 hspace=10 width=152 height=150></p>
<p><font size=5>Insert the lens holder into the condensor body until it aligns the 
red marquer on the photo.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti13img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=151 height=150><font size=5>Firmly screw the ring of the condensor body to 
ensure that the lens holder stays in place.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti14img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=151 height=120><font size=5>Deeply screw the adaptor holder into the 
condensor body.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti15img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=150 height=148><font size=5>Unsrew the adaptor holder.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti16img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=150 height=150><font size=5>Insert the condensor into the microscope 
mounting.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti17img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=150 height=150><font size=5>Screw and lock the adaptor holder.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><img src="ti18img0.gif" align=left border=2 hspace=10 width=150 height=151><font size=5>Adjust the elevation of the condensor as usual.</font></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<hr>
</body>

