<title>INJECTION TECHNIQUE OF THE 714X</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="ut14img0.gif">
<h1>Table of contents</h1>
<h3><a href="#step1">Preparing the necessay material</a> </h3>
<h3><a href="#step2">Preparing the Seringe</a> </h3>
<h3><a href="#step3">Getting the Patient ready</a> </h3>
<h3><a href="#step4">The Perinodulor injection</a> </h3>
<h3><a href="#step5">Sanitary precautions to be taken after the injection</a></h3>
<h3><a href="#step6">Particular cases</a></h3>
<hr>
<h1><a name="step1">Preparing the necessary material</a> </h1>
<p>- Multi-dose vial <a href="ti19img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> of 714X kept in the refrigerator (at about 4&#176;) </p>
<p>- Disposable 1cc 26G3/8 Tuberculine Seringe <a href="ti20img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> graded at 1/100 </p>
<p>- Sterile coton tampons </p>
<p>- Alcohol (94%) dispenser <a href="ti21img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> </p>
<p>- Small Ice Pak <a href="ti22img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> </p>
<p>- A container <a href="ti23img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> filled with methyl alcohol or bleach </p>
<p>- A tray that can hold all of the above </p>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="step2">Preparing the Seringe </a></h1>
<p><i>(At this point, washing and brushing hands is essential.)</i></p>
<ol>
<li>Get the seringe out of its sterile packaging. Make sure that the needle is fixed solidly and 
that the protective cover can easily be removed. </li>
<li>Take the multi-dose vial of 714X. Pull out the center of the metallic capsule (if the vial is 
new). Return to tray. </li>
<li>Take a sterile cotton tampon and soak it in alcohol at 94%. Disinfect the rubber lid 
(NEVER USE ISOPROPYL ALCOHOL). </li>
<li>Hold the vial in your left hand and put the needle through the center of the rubber lid. </li>
<li>Turn the vial and seringe upside down. <a href="ti24img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> Pull down the piston while making sure that 
the seringe receives 0.1cc more than the needed quantity <a href="ti08imga.htm">(depending upon the day of the 
cycle).</a> </li>
<li>Pull the seringe out of the multi-dose vial. </li>
<li>While holding the seringe with the needle toward the ceiling, pull the piston down to 
0.7cc. </li>
<li>Tap the seringe to dislodge and get the air bubbles out. </li>
<li>Push the piston to the required level. A small drop <a href="ti25img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> must appear at the end of the 
needle. </li>
<li>Put the protective cover back on the seringe and return it to the tray. </li>
</ol>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="step3">Getting the patient ready</a></h1>
<p><i>The injection must be performed in a room which allows for a certain degree of intimacy. 
The temperature must be comfortable.</i> </p>
<ol>
<li>The patient must lie down, his head held at a comfortable level. <a href="ti26img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> He or she must relax 
and abstain from wearing clothes that are too tight. </li>
<li>The lower part of the body must be nude except for underwear. </li>
<li>Put the ice pack on the right inguinal zone <a href="ti27img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> for a period of 10 minutes. The skin must 
take on a pink color. If the patient feels that the cold is too much of a shock on the skin, a 
paper towel can be placed between the skin and the Ice Pak. </li>
<li>Disinfect the injection zone with a sterile tampon soaked in 94% alcohol. </li>
</ol>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="step4">Perinodular injection</a></h1>
<ol>
<li>In the fold of the right leg, localize the pulse of the femoral artery. <a href="ti28img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> Place the 
middle-finger and the ring-finger on this artery and apply a progressive pressure to rise the 
deep lymphatic glands. The pulse of the artery is an important benchmark to localize the 
exact injection site. </li>
<li>With the side of your left hand, pull the skin of the lower belly toward the navel. </li>
<li>Rotate the wrist so that left hand's thumb is in front of the right hand fingers, pressing down 
on femoral artery. <a href="ti29img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> Replace the middle and ring fingers with thumb of left hand in 
order to maintain the pressure on the femoral artery and to assure that the lymph nodes do 
not slide back to their initial position. This pressure must be maintained througout the 
entire procedure; it assures that lymph nodes remain lightly elevated. </li>
<li>Now that it is free, the right hand can perform the injection. The exact site of the injection 
is 5 cm higher than the thumb on an imaginary line between the femoral artery and the 
navel. <a href="ti36img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> When the injection site is localized, the needle is inserted in a quick 
movement, and at needle-length depth. <a href="ti30img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> The left hand's thumb is then replaced by the 
right-hand's ring finger, to keep a good pressure on the artery, once again to avoid the 
receding of the lymph nodes. </li>
<li>The injection must be done very slowly. It should take between 10 and 20 minutes to inject 
0.5cc of 714X. During the injection, the seringe must be at a 45&#176; angle with the body. <a href="ti31img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> 
It is normal to feel pressure during the injection. If the pressure becomes too strong, it can 
be alleviated by simultaneously lifting the needle and the skin. If a burning sensation 
occurs, bring the Ice Pak close to the injection zone. </li>
<li>To limit the quantity of liquid injected with each depression of the plunger, one must avoid 
beaming down on the end part of the piston, but rather work a down movement with the 
left-hand on the side of the piston. The piston must go down about 1 milimeter each time. 
Repeat about every 10 seconds. </li>
<li>When the injection is over, wait 30 to 60 seconds before pulling out the needle. This will 
avoid a back flow of the 714X through the canal created by the needle, which would cause 
a burning sensation. </li>
<li>After having pulled out the needle, put a sterile cotton tampon on the injection site and put 
the Ice Pak back for fifteen minutes, directly on the injection zone. This will insure a better 
spreading of the product through the lymphatic system and diminish the risk of 
uncomfortable sensations caused by the rapid vaporization of 714X. The patient can take 
advantage of this time to relax before continuing his/her regular activities. </li>
<li>If a burning sensation reoccurs in the following hours, the skin can be cooled again with 
the Ice Pak or simply with ice. </li>
<li>If bleeding occurs after pulling out the needle, a bruise might appear. Such a situation is of 
no danger. </li>
</ol>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
<p><img src="ti32img0.gif" align=right hspace=0 width=300 height=225><a name="step5"><font size=6><strong>Sanitary precautions to be 
taken after the injection</strong></font></a></p>
<p><font size=5></font>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Put the seringe and the used needle in the container filled 
with methyl alcohol or bleach. All used tampons must 
also be put in that container. </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="step6">Particular cases</a></h1>
<p>Some patients might prefer to inject the 714X themselves. For self-injection, the position might 
vary. One might choose to lie down <a href="ti33img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> with pillows under his/her head or back, or one might 
prefer taking a half-sitting position. <a href="ti34img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> </p>
<p>The obese patient can help the person injecting the 714X by holding back the abdominal fat 
with his/her hands. <a href="ti35img0.gif"><img src="ut16img0.gif" align=absbottom border=0 width=40 height=25></a> In that manner, he uncovers the inguinal zone, site of the injection. </p>
<p><a href="#table">Return to Table of contents</a></p>
<hr>
</body>

