<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Arizona Caf&eacute; &amp; Grill</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF8F8F" BACKGROUND="acgback.jpg">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>ARIZONA CAFE &amp; GRILL</H1>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="acglogo.gif" ALT="Arizona Cafe and Grill" HEIGHT=222 WIDTH=146></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Guy Gabriel Coscas and Chef <A HREF="chrisbio.html">Christopher
Gross</A> are pleased to announce the opening of Arizona Caf&eacute; &amp;
Grill. This talented duo will work their collective restaurant magic at
the 32nd and Lincoln location, formerly known as Mother Tucker's. The spacious
main dining room is bordered with Indian blanketed booths and immense Arizona
state flag suspended from the ceiling. The centerpiece of this room is
the <I>Corral</I>, trimmed with lodgepole where diners will enjoy a bird's
eye view of the chef preparing trademark dishes exhibition style in the
pizza oven and rotisserie.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>A one of a kind view awaits guests who choose to dine
on ACG's covered patio. Arizona misters in the summer and a lovely outdoor
fireplace on crisp Valley evenings allow diners to enjoy great Arizona
cuisine and the fabulous Phoenix skyline. The lounge at ACG has already
become one of Phoenix's most high energy watering holes. ACG features a
marvelous wine list which is sure to include some of your favorites and
a unique collection of beers, imported and domestic, which are paired with
menu selections by Beverage Director, <A HREF="paola.html">Paola Gross</A>.
The lists feature a great variety of reasonably priced wine and beers guaranteed
to quench anyone's thirst.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>ACG will offer guests a true taste of Arizona. The menu
selections are moderately priced and the flavors are as vast as the Arizona
desert. Mouth watering starters and crisp salads are the perfect opening
for the menu headliners, sensational grilled steaks each accompanied by
three signature sauces, oven roasted pizzas and fabulous fresh fish. The
desserts are sweet, Arizona inspired interpretations of American favorites.
ACG's menu selections will tempt diners of all ages and is designed with
a casual family experience in mind.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>If ACG's food whets your appetite for all things Arizona,
then a trip to the ACG retail emporium is a must. The hottest souvenirs
in town and great gift items are available there, including ACG trademark
t-shirts, hats, jackets, and much, much more. Arizona Caf&eacute; &amp;
Grill has extensive facilities for special gatherings. A private dining
room features a traditional kiva fireplace and will accommodate 30 guests
comfortably. The combined facilities will seat up to 300 people.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>ACG is open daily at 11:00 AM serving lunch. Dinner will
be served nightly until 11:00 PM. Please call (602) 957-0777 for details
and reservations. For further information please contact Dawn Sullivan
at (602) 224-6708.</FONT></P>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>look at <A HREF="acgmenu.html">ACG's menu</A></FONT>
</LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>look at <A HREF="acgtogo.html">ACG's take out menu</A></FONT>
</LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com">Christopher's
Web Site</A> </FONT></LI>
</UL>

