<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christophers J. Gross</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg" BGCOLOR="#ffff80" TEXT="#800040" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#8000ff" ALINK="#ff8000">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Christopher J. Gross</H1>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="candp.jpg" HEIGHT=316 WIDTH=206></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Christopher and Paola Gross</H3>

<P><B>Christopher Gross began his culinary career at the early age of 14
in Phoenix, Arizona and has since perfected his skills throughout Europe
and the United States. Christopher has been associated with such fine restaurants
as <I>Chez Albert</I>, Paris; <I>L'Orangerie</I> and <I>Century Plaza Hotel</I>,
Los Angeles; and <I>La Champagne</I> and <I>Le Relais</I>, Scottsdale,
Arizona.</B></P>

<P><B>In 1988, Christopher was one of 12 chefs in America, and the only
chef from Arizona, to compete in the <I>1988 Bocuse d'Or</I> Competition
in Chicago. Christopher's accomplishments have created a worldwide reputation
and have garnered for him the respect of his peers nationally and internationally.
In July, 1989, Christopher was named one of America's 10 Best New Chefs
by Food and Wine Magazine. These annual awards are designed to recognize
the very best talent of America's new generation of chefs. The search for
the 1989 winners began one year prior with a roster of over 400 nominees
proposed by the Food and Wine editors, as well as 149 restaurant critics,
food writers and chefs nationwide who were polled by the magazine. Christopher
was featured in the August 1989 issue of Food and Wine which was dedicated
to the awards.</B></P>

<P><B>In January 1990, Christopher opened his most noteworthy venture to
date. &quot;<I>Christopher's</I> and <I>Christopher's Bistro</I>&quot;
located in the prestigious Biltmore area of Phoenix opened to rave reviews.
A unique dining experience awaits each and every guest. Guests at <I>Christopher's</I>
enjoy classical yet innovative cuisine amid the sophisticated elegance
which epitomizes Christopher's style. Christopher's art is evident in the
<I>Bistro</I> as well. The finest and freshest ingredients, deceptively
simple preparations and exquisite presentations are Christopher's trademarks.
</B></P>

<P><B>Christopher founded the Arizona Chapter of the American Institute
of Wine and Food, and served as chairman of the Julia Child and Mondavi
organization.</B></P>

<P><B>The prestigious James Beard Foundation has honored Christopher repeatedly.
As the guest chef for numerous Beard functions beginning in 1989, Christopher's
culinary productions have been heralded as &quot;<I>planned, perfectly
executed and wildly imaginative</I>&quot;. Twice nominated as Best Chef
of the Southwest for the James Beard Awards, Christopher hosted a spectacular
dinner at the restaurant to benefit the Beard Foundation at which all previous
records for proceeds raised were shattered. Additionally, he is a member
of the Beard Foundation's National Advisory Board. </B></P>

<P><B>During the early summer of 1994, Christopher filmed a show for the
award winning series, <I>In Julia's Kitchen with Master Chefs</I>, featuring
world - renowned cooking authority Julia Child. Julia and Christopher prepared
several of Chef Christopher's favorite recipes, which will also be featured
in the new bestseller In <I>Julia's Kitchen with Master Chefs</I>. Christopher
is currently featured weekly on the number - one rated morning show of
the Phoenix area's leading independent station Good Morning Arizona and
Christopher's wife, Paola, writes for Andre Gayot's TASTES.</B> </P>

<P><B>The culinary arts, charitable organizations of all designations have
been the recipients of Christopher's dedication. Appearing as a guest chef
at multitudes of functions locally and throughout the country, Christopher's
gastronomic efforts have benefited the March of Dimes, Red Cross Flood
Relief, Share our Strength, the Arizona Liver Alliance, the Phoenix Art
Museum, the Hospice of Cincinnati, Hurricane Relief Fund, Heartland Flood
Relief. </B></P>

<P><B>In December 1994, Christopher with partner Guy Coscas opened a fabulous
new restaurant. Christopher designed a relaxed family-oriented menu featuring
Western comfort foods at moderate prices. <I>Arizona Cafe &amp; Grill</I>,
locally known as ACG, was an immediate hit with Phoenix natives and Valley
visitors alike and is currently Phoenix's favorite watering hole.</B></P>

<P><B>In 1995, Christopher was honored for his consistent culinary excellence
as he was named the 1995 <I>Perrier Jou&euml;t Best Chef of the Southwest</I>
at the James Beard Awards. This coveted honor places Christopher among
the culinary elite in America. Also in 1995 Christopher's was inducted
into the Nation's Restaurant News Fine Dining Hall of Fame. With this induction
Christopher's joins a group of industry counterparts selected for this
unique distinction. </B></P>

<P><B>In June of 1993, Christopher married <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/paola.html">Paola
Embry</A>. Paola's talent, commitment to excellence &amp; education have
made her a natural for the position of &quot;<I>Wine &amp; Service Director</I>&quot;
at <I>Christopher's</I> and <I>Christopher's Bistro</I>. </B></P>

<CENTER><P><B><I>Christopher's</I> is located at:<BR>
Biltmore Financial Center (Lobby Level)<BR>
2398 East Camelback Road<BR>
Phoenix, Arizona 85016<BR>
phone: (602) 957-3214</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>email: <A HREF="mailto:dine@christophers.com">dine@christophers.com</A></B></P></CENTER>

<P><B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/chris.html">Christophers
Restaurant<BR>
</A>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

