<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Paola Gross, Wine Director</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Paola Millen Gross</H1>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="paola.jpg" HEIGHT=234 WIDTH=183></P></CENTER>

<P><B>Born and raised in the Vina Del Mar region of Chile, Paola Millen
Gross' indefatigable commitment to the science of the grape is not surprising.
Mrs. Gross' pursuit of excellence for herself and her clients is broadbased
and thorough. </B></P>

<P><B>During a lengthy tenure with Halstead and Associates, both in Europe
and in this country, Paola served as a consultant to various food and hospitality
industry. From hypermarkets to acclaimed restaurants, Paola provided these
operations needed expertise regarding the buying and stocking of wines.
This time also provided a rich and once in a lifetime learning environment
for Paola. Paola continued her education upon her return to this country.
Beginning in 1992 Paola assumed the position as <I>Wine Director</I> of
the internationally acclaimed restaurants, <I>Christopher's</I> and <I>Christopher's
Bistro</I>. Under Paola's direction the list at Christopher's has garnered
the prestigious <I>Wine Spectator</I> Best Award of Excellence repeatedly.
As director, Paola designs, implements and maintains their award winning
list. Paola also manages all the operations for <I>Christopher's Cellar</I>,
a retail wine shop located on premise at Christopher's. </B></P>

<P><B>In 1994, Paola also took the reins as the Director for <A HREF="wine.html">Christopher's
Wine and Cigar Club</A>. Here, Paola maintains the private cellars of the
membership as well as purchasing all wines and cigars. In addition to these
myriad duties Paola is the Beverage Director for the newly opened Arizona
Cafe &amp; Grill. In this capacity Paola has designed and executed a unique
program of matching wine and beer with each menu selection as well as creating
and implementing extensive lists for each.</B></P>

<P><B>Paola's vast expertise has led to numerous new opportunities: she
has authored a monthly column on the art of wine and food for a popular
national publication, &quot;<I>Guest West</I>&quot; and is a regular contributor
to &quot;<I>The Wine Authority</I>&quot;. At present she writes for &quot;<I>Andre
Gayot's TASTES</I>&quot; and has published pieces in several Arizona publications.
Paola and Christopher are quite active in broadcast media including a food
and wine feature on the highly acclaimed <I>Good Morning Arizona</I>.</B></P>

<P><B>Paola has been honored for her extensive knowledge of the art and
science of vintage wines. She has received the <I>Certificat de M&eacute;rite</I>
from <I>Les Comit&eacute; National des Vins de France, </I>a <I>Degree
of Honor</I> from <I>Les Amis du Vin International Wine Society</I> and
most recently one of a select few to be inducted into the prestigious <I>Confr&eacute;rie
des Amis du Bontemps</I> in Bordeaux, France.</B></P>

<P><B>In June 1993 Paola married renowned Chef Christopher Gross. As a
team, Paola and Christopher have originated a unique concept utilizing
their collective expertise, wine and food matching seminars. Clients such
as Seven Seas Cruise Lines, Club Med and Crystal Cruises have delighted
their guests with the enthusiasm and knowledge that Paola and Christopher
bring to the seminars.</B></P>

<P></P>


<P><B>
<A HREF="chilestill.html">Chile... still hot</A> an article by Paola Gross<BR>
Back to <A HREF="cellar.html">Christopher's Wine Cellar</A><BR>
Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com">Christopher's Web Site</A>
</B></P>

