<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>DESSERT OF LAURA CHENEL'S FROMAGE BLANC</H2>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>WITH HONEY, OLIVE OIL, FIGS AND CONFIT OF VANILLA BEANS</H2>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><I>serves 4</I></H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>12 oz. Fromage Blanc </B></LI>

<LI><B>4 Figs cut in thirds </B></LI>

<LI><B>6 Medium Strawberries cut in half </B></LI>

<LI><B>4-6 oz. Honey-Olive Sauce (See recipe) </B></LI>

<LI><B>4 Vanilla Beans, sliced thin in Julienne and Confit</B></LI>

<LI><B>4 Pieces Biscotti (See recipe) </B></LI>

<LI><B>4 Pieces Mint </B></LI>
</UL>

<H3>Honey-Olive Sauce:</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>3 oz. Warm Honey </B></LI>

<LI><B>3 oz. Olive Oil </B></LI>

<LI><B>Seeds of Vanilla Beans </B></LI>
</UL>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Warm honey with infused with
seeds from vanilla beans for thirty minutes (30) just heating gently.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>3 ounces of olive oil mixed
in the blender with honey (mix at last minute to keep infused).</B> </P>

<H3>Vanilla Confit:</H3>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>You may use fresh beans. When
making with fresh beans wash them and slice into very thin strips.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Place them in 1/2 cup sugar
and 1/2 cup water to make a simple syrup. Cook for one hour. You may need
to replace the water from time to time as it may reduce too much and caramelize.
</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Cook until tender. Remove
the strips and roll in sugar and let dry.</B></P>

<H3>Biscotti:</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>2 cups Dried Figs or any other dried fruit </B></LI>

<LI><B>6 oz. Orange flavored Liqueur </B></LI>

<LI><B>9 cups All purpose Flour </B></LI>

<LI><B>3 cups Sugar </B></LI>

<LI><B>1 tbsp Baking Soda </B></LI>

<LI><B>1 tsp. Salt </B></LI>

<LI><B>1 1/3 cup Fresh Orange Juice </B></LI>

<LI><B>1 cup Honey </B></LI>

<LI><B>4 tbsp Freshly grated orange zest </B></LI>

<LI><B>2 tsp Vanilla </B></LI>

<LI><B>2 1/2 cup Almonds </B></LI>

<LI><B>1 cup Olive oil </B></LI>
</UL>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>In one bowl mix all dry ingredients
plus chopped fruit.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>In another bowl mix all the
liquids</B>.</P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Add the liquids to the dry
ingredients. Kneed for about five minutes. Then let rest in cooler for
approximately ten minutes.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Roll the dough out into rectangles
1 cm. thick and 6 &quot; wide.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>Bake at 350 degrees until
golden brown but not dry. Then place in the cooler to cool.</B></P>

<P><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40><B>When cool, slice in thin strips.
Place on sheet pan and bake until crisp.</B> </P>

<H3>Presentation:</H3>

<P><B>Place three scoops of cheese in center. Orange fruit around cheese;
then drizzle the sauce around. Complete the garnishing with confit vanilla,
biscotti and mint.</B> </P>

<BR>

<P><B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

