<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Hot &amp; Cold Chocolate</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b6Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>HOT &amp; COLD CHOCOLATE</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 8 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=CENTER>CHOCOLATE ICE CREAM:</H2>

<UL>
<LI>5 EGG YOLKS</LI>

<LI>5 OZ SUGAR</LI>

<LI>1 PT MILK</LI>

<LI>3 OZ CREAM</LI>

<LI>1.5 OZ COCOA</LI>

<LI>4 OZ CHOCOLATE, DARK SEMI-SWEET</LI>
</UL>

<P>WHISK EGG YOLKS, SUGAR AND COCOA TOGETHER THEN ADD BOILING MILK AND
CREAM.<BR>
MIX AND THEN RETURN TO HEAT. COOK UNTIL SAUCE THICKENS, BE VERY CAREFUL
SAUCE DOES NOT BREAK, THEN REMOVE FROM HEAT AND ADD CHOCOLATE.<BR>
ALLOW CHOCOLATE TO MELT. WHEN MELTED STRAIN AND FREEZE IN ICE CREAM MACHINE
ACCORDING TO MANUFACTURER'S INSTRUCTIONS.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=CENTER>CHOCOLATE TART</H2>

<UL>
<LI>5 OZ BUTTER, MELTED</LI>

<LI>5 OZ CHOCOLATE, MELTED</LI>

<LI>5 EGGS</LI>

<LI>6.5 OZ SUGAR</LI>

<LI>1.25 OZ PASTRY FLOUR</LI>
</UL>

<P>WHISK EGGS AND SUGAR TIL THICK. ADD MELTED CHOCOLATE AND BUTTER. FOLD
IN FLOUR.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=CENTER>ESPRESSO SAUCE:</H2>

<UL>
<LI>8 OZ CREAM</LI>

<LI>1/2 VANILLA BEAN</LI>

<LI>4 EGG YOLKS</LI>

<LI>2 OZ ESPRESSO BEANS</LI>
</UL>

<P>BRING CREAM AND VANILLA BEAN TO BOIL WITH ESPRESSO BEAN. MIX EGG YOLKS
AND TEMPER WITH 1/3 BOILING CREAM. COMBINE EGG AND CREAM MIXTURE WITH REMAINING
2/3 CREAM AND CONTINUE COOKING, WHISKING AT ALL TIMES. AFTER CREAM THICKENS,
STRAIN.</P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=CENTER>DARK CHOCOLATE
SAUCE:</H2>

<P>SPLIT THE ESPRESSO SAUCE IN HALF AND WHILE WARM ADD 2 OZ OF CHOPPED
DARK CHOCOLATE AND MIX TIL MELTED AND DISSOLVED IN SAUCE.</P>

<P>MOLD CHOCOLATE ICE CREAM IN A ROUND RING 3&quot; IN DIAMETER AND REFREEZE.
PLACE ANOTHER RING OF THE SAME SIZE ON A BAKING SHEET. FILL WITH TART MIX
1 INCH HIGH. BAKE AT 375 DEGREES TIL DONE, APPROXIMENTLY 3 MINUTES.<BR>
SHOULD BE LIQUID ON THE INSIDE, BE VERY CAREFUL WHEN UNMOLDING AND THAT
MOLD HAD BEEN LIGHTLY BUTTERED OR SPRAYED WITH A NON-STICK SPRAY.</P>

<H3>TO ASSEMBLE:</H3>

<P>UNMOLD ICE CREAM RING IN CENTER OF CHILLED PLATE. PLACE JUST BAKED (HOT)
TART ATOP ICE CREAM. SERVE IMMEDIATELY.</P>

<P>SAUCE WITH ESPRESSO AND CHOCOLATE SAUCE AROUND DESSERT.</P>

<P>WINES TO BE SERVED WITH THIS RECIPE:<BR>
MUSCAT DE BEAUMES-DE-VENISE, DURBAN 1991<BR>
BANYULS. DOMAINE DU MAS BLANC 1982 RESERVE (FRANCE)</P>

<P><BR>
</P>

