<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Salmon en Cro&ucirc;te</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg" BGCOLOR="#ffff80" TEXT="#800040" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#8000ff" ALINK="#ff8000">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe"></CENTER>

<H1>SALMON EN CRO&Ucirc;TE</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 8 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"> INGREDIENTS</H2>
<UL>
<LI>1 lb Salmon</LI>
<LI>4 oz Scallops</LI>
<LI>4 oz Cream</LI>
<LI>2 sheets of pie dough, puff pastry or equivalent of phillo dough (12 inches x 8 inches</LI>
<LI>1 beaten egg</LI>
<LI>salt &amp; pepper</LI>
<LI>2 tbs chopped chives</LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"> PREPARATION</H2>

<P>2 / 8 oz filets seasoned with salt &amp; pepper</P>

<H3>Mousse:</H3>
<P>Puree in a processor scallops, then add cream, salt, pepper and
<I>remove</I>, add herbs.</P>

<P>Place fish filets on plastic wrap twice the size of the fish -
spread on mousse and top with the other filet - roll filets in
plastic firmly and tie each end securely - cook in simmering water
for 15 minutes or until done, remove and cool in ice water till cold.
(approximately 10 minutes) Remove fish from plastic.</P>

<H3>Rewrap the filet loosely  and do not tie the ends!!!</H3>

<P>Place on pastry - brush pastry with egg and place 2nd piece of
pastry on top - sealing fish in plastic inside pastry.<BR>
Brush pastry with remaining egg and decorate (cut pastry to look
like a fish).<P>

<P>Place in oven, bake at 350 degrees till pastry is nice and brown -
about 15 minutes.<P>

<H3>Serve with a Chardonnay.</H3>

<BR>

<P><B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

