<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Seabass in tomato consomm&eacute;</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>SEABASS&nbsp;IN&nbsp;TOMATO CONSOMM&Eacute;<BR>
WITH TOMATO&nbsp;MOUSSE</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 4 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>INGREDIENTS</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>8 pieces of thinly sliced seabass</B></LI>

<LI><B>6 ripe tomatoes</B></LI>

<LI><B>salt &amp; pepper</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 garlic clove</B></LI>

<LI><B>1/2 cup fresh herbs, chervil, tarragon, basil, etc</B></LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PREPARATION</H2>

<UL>
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<LI><B>Puree in a Blender or juice in Juicer 6 ripe tomatoes with salt
&amp; pepper, garlic clove &amp;&nbsp;fresh herbs.</B><BR>
</LI>

<LI><B>Place juice in stainless steel sauce pot, bring to simmer, simmer
for 10 minutes.</B><BR>
</LI>

<LI><B>Remove gently the red tomato mousse with a skimmer (the red foam
mousse will float to the top leaving a clear consomm&eacute; underneath).</B><BR>
</LI>

<LI><B>Season consomm&eacute; with salt &amp;&nbsp;pepper, you may also
add a clove of garlic &amp;&nbsp;infuse for five minutes, then strain.</B><BR>
</LI>

<LI><B>Use this consomm&eacute; as a soup to poach fish in.</B><BR>
</LI>

<LI><B>Use the tomato mousse to garnish dish by forming quenelles with
spoons to make egg shapes for garnish.</B></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<P><BR>
</P>

<P><B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web
Site</A></B></P>

<P><B><I><FONT SIZE=-1>designed and hosted by <A HREF="http://www.grouper.com/">Grouper
Technologies</A></FONT></I></B></P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
