<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Southwest vegetable stew</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>SOUTHWEST VEGETABLE STEW<BR>
(SOUTHWEST FRANCE)</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 4 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>INGREDIENTS</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>1 medium egg plant - diced medium</B></LI>

<LI><B>4 zucchini - diced medium</B></LI>

<LI><B>4 red bell peppers - diced medium</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 green bell peppers - diced medium</B></LI>

<LI><B>6 roma tomatoes - chopped &amp;&nbsp;seeded</B></LI>

<LI><B>3 cloves of garlic - crushed</B></LI>

<LI><B>6 fresh leafs of basil</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 tbs. extra virgin olive oil for saut&eacute;ing vegetables</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 cup extra virgun olive oil for sauce</B></LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PREPARATION</H2>

<UL>
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<LI><B>Saut&eacute; all diced vegetables, garlic, thyme &amp;&nbsp;basil
in 2 tbs. olive oil in a very hot pan for 1 minute.</B></LI>

<LI><B>Remove 1/2 vegetable mixture &amp;&nbsp;place in a juicer with 1/2
the tomatoes.</B></LI>

<LI><B>Extract juice, place in a pan &amp;&nbsp;reduce by 1/2 to concentrate
flavors, then place in blender &amp;&nbsp;slowly add olive oil to emulsify
with sauce.</B></LI>

<LI><B>Season with salt &amp;&nbsp;pepper and reserve</B></LI>

<LI><B>With remaining vegetable continue to cook till tender.</B></LI>

<LI><B>Add remaining chopped tomatoes &amp;&nbsp;season to taste.</B></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<P><B>Divide by 4, placing in center of plate &amp;&nbsp;ladle sauce around
- you may garnish with extra fresh basil leafs or zucchini blossoms (flowers).</B></P>

<H3>This dish may be:</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>Served hot or cold</B></LI>

<LI><B>Used as a side dish for fish or meats</B></LI>

<LI><B>If you have leftovers you may add 1 cup of broth (more or less for
desired consistency) &amp; place in blender to make a soup - also good
served hot or cold.</B><BR>
</LI>
</UL>

<H3>Recomended wine:&nbsp;Pinot Noir</H3>

<P><BR>
<B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

<P><B><I><FONT SIZE=-1>designed and hosted by <A HREF="http://www.grouper.com/">Grouper
Technologies</A></FONT></I></B></P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
