<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Grilled Portobello Salad</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>GRILLED PORTOBELLO SALAD</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 4 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>INGREDIENTS</H2>

<H3>Portobello Salad</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>4 medium portobello</B></LI>
<LI><B>8 cups cleaned field greens (aragula, oak-leaf, mizuna, tot soi,
lola rosa, etc, you may substitute Romaine)</B></LI>
</UL>

<H3>Dressing</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>2 oz aged balsamic vinegar</B></LI>
<LI><B>8 oz extra virgin olive oil</B></LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PREPARATION</H2>

<UL>
<UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<LI><B>Dressing: mix oil &amp; vinegar. Add salt &amp;&nbsp;pepper to taste.</B></LI>
<LI><B>Garnish: reduce by half <FONT SIZE=-1>1/2 </FONT>cup of aged balsamic
vinegar</B></LI>
<LI><B>Brush mushroom with olive oil and grill on both sides 2-3 minutes
each side (may also saut&eacute; in pan).</B></LI>
<LI><B>Add sea salt and fresh ground pepper.</B></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<P><B>Place salad greens atop a plate, warm grill mushroom at bottom and
dress the garnish of reduced balsamic around plate.</B></P>

<P><BR>
<B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

