<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Chocolate Cigar with Vanilla Armagnac Ice Cream</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>CHOCOLATE CIGAR WITH<BR>
VANILLA ARMAGNAC ICE CREAM</H1>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>INGREDIENTS</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>5 <FONT SIZE=-1>1/2</FONT> ounces dark chocolate</B></LI>

<LI><B>3 tbsp butter, unsalted</B></LI>

<LI><B><FONT SIZE=-1>1/4 </FONT>cup whipping cream</B></LI>

<LI><B>10 egg whites, whipped stiff</B></LI>

<LI><B>4 tbsp superfine sugar</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 large sheet parchment paper</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 ounces dark chocolate, melted</B></LI>

<LI><B>5 ounces white chocolate, melted</B></LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PREPARATION</H2>

<P><B>Place 5 <FONT SIZE=-1>1/2</FONT> ounces of the dark chocolate and
3 tablespoons butter in a medium bowl and place on top of the stove in
a water bath. The water should just simmer. While the chocolate and butter
are melting, stir with a wooden spoon occasionally to mix. This should
take about 5 minutes. At the same time with a hand held mixer or whip,
in a medium bowl beat the heavy cream until stiff. Set aside. To finish
the mousse, fold the chocolate and egg whites together, then fold the cream
with a spatula.</B></P>

<P><B>You will need one large sheet of parchment paper, tape and a pastry
bag. Cut parchment paper in strips approximently 8&quot; x 6&quot;. (This
size will enable you to &quot;double wrap&quot; the sides for strength.)
Roll out strips into a tube approximently on inch in diameter and tape.
Stand them up and fill with the chocolate mousse using the pastry bag.
(They stand nicely in a coffee tin.) They are to be placed in the freezer
until frozen.</B></P>

<P><B>Melt dark and milk chocolate and mix together (but not too much,
just enough to get a wood grain effect or in this case tints or shades
of color in the tobacco leaf.) Spread thinly on a sheet of plastic approximently
4&quot; x 6&quot; as the length and diameter of the chocolate mousse. Then
unwrap frozen mousse and wrap plastic around the mousse and place in the
refrigerator for approximently 2 minutes until the chocolate hardens. Then
you may unwrap and let defrost in the refrigerator so that the mousse softens.
</B></P>

<P><B>To make the cigar band, cut a stencil in the shape of a cigar band
to match the circumference of the cigar. Give yourself a little extra length
so when you cook the cigarette paste and wrap around a wooden or plastic
dowel. </B></P>

<H3><B>Cigarette Paste: (Cigar Band)</B></H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>3 cups Egg Whites</B></LI>

<LI><B>4 ounces Sugar</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 &frac14; ounces Flour</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 &frac14; ounces Butter, Melted </B></LI>
</UL>

<P><B>Small pastry bad or triangle of parchment paper rolled into a cone.
</B></P>

<H3><B>Ice Cream:</B></H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>2 cups Half &amp; Half</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 cups Milk</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 Vanilla Bean, Split</B></LI>

<LI><B>8 Egg Yolk</B></LI>

<LI><B>1 cup Granulated Sugar </B></LI>
</UL>

<OL>
<LI><B>For the ice cream base, slowly bring the half &amp; half, milk and
vanilla bean to a boil</B></LI>

<LI><B>In a stainless steel bowl, whisk together egg yolks with the sugar.</B></LI>

<LI><B>Whisk in &frac14; of the scalded milk and half &amp; half into the
egg mixture to temper the yolks</B></LI>

<LI><B>Pour in the remaining milk &amp; cook, while stirring constantly,
over a double boiler, until the custard coats the back of the spoon</B></LI>

<LI><B>Strain out the vanilla bean and cool to 40 degrees 6) Add &frac14;
cup chopped prunes that have been marinated in Armagnac overnight </B></LI>
</OL>

<H3>Illycaffe Espresso Sauce:</H3>

<UL>
<LI><B>8 Egg Yolks</B></LI>

<LI><B>3 &frac12; ounces Sugar</B></LI>

<LI><B>2 cups Half &amp; Half</B></LI>

<LI><B>&frac12; Vanilla Bean</B></LI>

<LI><B>&frac12;Tbsp Vanilla Extract</B></LI>

<LI><B>3 ounces Illycaffe Espresso Beans </B></LI>
</UL>

<P><B>For the espresso sauce, with a hand held mixer, cream the yolks and
sugar in a medium bowl. At the same time bring the half &amp; half with
the vanilla bean to a simmer in a medium sauce pot. When the half &amp;
half is hot, temper the egg yolk and sugar mixture by adding &frac14; cup
hot half &amp; half. Stir well. Pour the egg and sugar mixture into the
rest of the half &amp; half with the espresso beans and cook gently over
a low heat stirring constantly. When the sauce is thick enough to coat
the back of the spoon, strain and let cool. </B></P>
<B></B>
<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PRESENTATION</H2>

<P><B>Garnish with fresh fruit, raspberries and blackberries or whatever
is in season.</B></P>

<P><B>Place ice cream in ashtray then the cigar. Garnish with fruit and
mint and espresso sauce on the bottom of the plate. </B></P>

<P><BR>
<B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

<P><B><I><FONT SIZE=-1>designed and hosted by <A HREF="http://www.grouper.com/">Grouper
Technologies</A></FONT></I></B></P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
