<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Apple Tart</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>APPLE TART</H1>

<P><B><I>YIELD: 20 SERVINGS</I></B></P>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>INGREDIENTS</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>24 green apples, cored & sliced thin</B></LI>
<LI><B>8 oz butter, melted</B></LI>
<LI><B>8 oz sugar</B></LI>
<LI><B>18 oz pastry flour or cake flour</B></LI>
<LI><B>9 oz butter, unsalted, cut in small pieces</B></LI>
<LI><B>2 eggs</B></LI>
<LI><B>4 oz cold water</B></LI>
<LI><B>pinch of salt</B></LI>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>PREPARATION</H2>

<UL><UL TYPE=SQUARE>
<LI><B>Combine flour, salt, butter & eggs in processor & turn on
add water & stop machine - do not over mix - if needed finish mixing by hand
refrigerate dough for 1 hour before using roll very thin</B></LI>

<LI><B>Cut out a circle with a salad plate for the diameter
arrange apple slices, fanned out, around the tart dough</B></LI>

<LI><B>Top with 1 oz sugar</B></LI>

<LI><B>Bake @ 350 degrees on parchment paper for about 10 minutes, or until brown</B></LI>

<LI><B>Garnish with strawberry flower and mint leaves</B></LI>

<LI><B>Serve slightly whipped cream on the side</B></LI>
</UL></UL>

<H3>Caramel Sauce:</H3>
<UL>
<LI><B>2 lbs sugar</B></LI>
<LI><B>12 oz water</B></LI>
<LI><B>2 pt cream</B></LI>
</UL>

<P><B>Bring sugar & water to a boil & cook till caramelizes. Stop cooking by
adding the cream & cook slowly until all the sugar dissolves</B></P>

