<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Christopher's Recipes: Traditional Yule Log</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#800040" BGCOLOR="#FFFF80" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#8000FF" ALINK="#FF8000" BACKGROUND="chrisbg.jpg">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="recipe.gif" ALT="Christopher's Recipe" HEIGHT=60 WIDTH=166></P></CENTER>

<H1>TRADITIONAL YULE LOG</H1>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>FOR CHOCOLATE MOUSSE</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>24 oz semi-sweet chocolate (block)</B></LI>
<LI><B>24 oz heavy cream</B></LI>
<LI><B>16 oz heavy cream</B></LI>
<P><B>Chop chocolate into small bits &amp; place into metal bowl<BR>
Bring heavy cream up to a boil<BR>
Pour over chocolate and mix with a whisk until smooth<BR>
REFRIGERATE 24 HOURS<BR>
THE NEXT DAY:<BR>
Whip 16 oz of heavy cream with the chocolate mixture<BR>
YOU MOUSSE IS DONE</B></P>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>FOR GANACHE ICING</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>16 oz semi-sweet chocolate (block)</B></LI>
<LI><B>16 oz heavy cream</B></LI>
<P><B>Chop chocolate into small pieces and place into metal bowl<BR>
Bring heavy cream up to a boil and pour over chocolate. Whisk until smooth.<BR>
*** Chief's Tip ***<BR>
When working with cream be careful not to over whisk. Cream will turn to butter
if you over whisked!!!</B></P>
</UL>

<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>FOR BISQUIT (WHITE)</H2>

<UL>
<LI><B>9 egg yolks</B></LI>
<LI><B><FONT SIZE=-1>1/2 </FONT>cup plus 3 tbs of sugar</B></LI>
<P><B>beat until stiff</B></P>
<LI><B>9 egg whites</B></LI>
<P><B>beat until stiff</B></P>
<P><B>fold yolks/sugar and whites together</B></P>
<LI><B><FONT SIZE=-1>1/4 </FONT>cup pastry flour</B></LI>
<LI><B><FONT SIZE=-1>1/4 </FONT>cup ground almonds</B></LI>
<P><B>fold into above</B></P>
<LI><B>4 oz melted butter</B></LI>
<P><B>pour into above an gently mix by hand</B></P>
<P><B>*** FOR CHOCOLATE ***</B></P>
<P><B>fold in 3<FONT SIZE=-1>1/2</FONT> tbs cocoa powder</B></P>
<P><B>Bake in a 350 degree oven until a toothpick inserted comes out moist but not wet.<BR>
Cool.</B></P>
</UL>


<H2><IMG SRC="circ.gif" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=40 ALIGN=TEXTTOP>TO ASSEMBLE</H2>

<OL>
<LI><B>Lay plastic wrap out on counter (use more than one sheet depending
on width you desire)</B></LI>
<LI><B>When cake has cooled, lay on top of plastic wrap</B></LI>
<LI><B>Spread mousse on top of cake</B></LI>
<LI><B>Roll, while using the plastic wrap as your support, and guide roll
up the cake into a nice even log</B></LI>
<LI><B>Trim away any excess cake with a knife</B></LI>
<LI><B>Freeze cake for a few hours</B></LI>
<LI><B>Pipe on ganache, as demonstrated by chef Christopher Gross</B></LI>
<LI><B>Cut and present</B></LI>
</OL>
<UL>
<P><B>*** Chief's Tip ***<BR>
Keep in mind that all ingredients must be at the proper temperatures and
consistencies to properly assemble any culinary delight! Bon Apetit!</B></P>
</UL>

<P><BR>
<B>Back to <A HREF="http://www.christophers.com/">Christopher's Web Site</A></B></P>

<P><B><I><FONT SIZE=-1>designed and hosted by <A HREF="http://www.grouper.com/">Grouper
Technologies</A></FONT></I></B></P>

</BODY>
