<Title> JPL 1st Quarter Report - FY'96 </Title>

 <A HREF="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/">
	<h2>JET PROPULSION LABORATORY </h2></A>

<H2>Introduction </H2>

<h4>	<! Never terminated, makes the entire report bold-face! >

This report describes the progress made during the first quarter of FY 1996
(from October 1 to December 31, 1995) and the plans for the next quarter 
in the JPL Telerobotics program.<P>

The JPL Telerobotics program is organized into three work elements with a
varying number of tasks for each:<P>

<UL>
<LI> On-orbit Assembly:
        <UL>
        <LI> <a href="#rdac">	Ranger Dexterous Arm Control </a>
								<!Seraji>
        <LI> <a href="#ravi">	Ranger Automated Visual Inspection </a>
								<!Kim>
        <LI> <a href="#sview">	Calibrated Synthetic Viewing </a>
								<!Kim>
	<LI> <a href="#lmma">	Low Mass, Compact Muscle Actuators</a>
								<!Bar-Cohen>
        </UL>
<P>
<LI> Exploration Robotics:
        <UL>
        <LI> <a href="#lsr">	Lightweight and Survivable Rover</a> <!Schenker>
        <LI> <a href="#lrsr">	Long-Range Science Rover</a>	<!Hayati>
        <LI> <a href="#pat">	Planetary Aerobot Testbed</a>	<!Nock>
        <LI> <a href="#nrtd">	Nanorover Technology Development</a>
								<!Wilcox>
        <LI> <a href="#esb">	Exploration of Small Bodies</a>	<!Sevilla>
        <LI> <a href="#mldm">	Micro-Lander Dexterous Manipulation</a>
								<!Schenker>
        <LI> <a href="#vtgg">	Vision and Touch Guided Grasping (MIT)</a>
								<!MIT>
        <LI> <a href="#me">	Mars Exploration (MIT) </a>	<!Brooks>
        </UL>
<P>
<LI> Terrestrial & Commercial Applications:
        <UL>
	<LI> <a href="#rams">	MicroTelerobotics & Medical Applications </a>
				<!Robotics Assisted Microsurgery (RAMS)>
								<!Das>
        </UL>
</UL>

<!HR>

More on 
<A HREF="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/">
	JPL Robotics</A>
