<H3>D. Contracts:</H3><BR>

<DL>
<DT><B>USC:</B>

<DD>The work focused on the experimental evaluation of benchmarking
methods developed to date, consisting primarily of sending the
rover on repeated sorties, and measuring various navigation performance
metrics with the use of optical, proximity and contact sensors.
 During the quarter, the rovers were instrumented  to enrich the
data resulting from the experiments.  Current focus is on interpreting
and drawing conclusions from the collected data.   


<DT><B>Lockheed-Martin:</B>

<DD>The work focused on outdoor testing of the Wide Angle Sun
Sensor prototype, to verify repeatability, determine sensitivity
to variations in various solar illumination conditions, and to
establish performance calibration parameters.  Performance to
date is satisfactory, but additional tests are now being conducted
to determine absolute sensor accuracy, using an improved experimental
procedure to compare the measured vs. true sun location.

</DL>

