<a name="rdac">

<H2>Ranger Dexterous Arm Control </H2>

The goal of this task is to augment the operational capabilities of the
dexterous arms in the Ranger Flight Experiment.  These new capabilities will
be developed within the framework of Configuration Control, which has been
developed at JPL and selected for implementation on the Ranger arms.
The FY'95 focus was to develop and implement collision detection and
avoidance capabilities for the Ranger arms, and to transfer the software
to the Ranger project.  The FY'96 focus is to develop, simulate and transfer
the automated base placement capability for the Ranger, and to conduct 
experiments to validate the collision detection/avoidance and base
placement capabilities.
<p>

<IMG SRC="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/people/hayati/Quarterly_Reports/ranger.gif">

<H3> A. Activities in This Reporting Period </H3>
<UL>

<LI> Replanned the task, including scope, schedule and staffing changes, to 
absorb a $100K FY '96 budget cut.  In particular, this included delaying the
implementation of optimal base placement (see Schedule, below).
<P>

<LI> Completed implementation of obstacle detection as an independent
task as requested by SSL, and began integration
into the JPL RSI laboratory for test and validation.
<P>

<LI> Developed and presented a new TRIWG proposal on Ranger Autonomy.
<P>

<LI> Attended and presented at the Ranger Integrated Design 
Review #2, April 3-5, at the University of Maryland.
<P>

<LI> A paper entitled "On-Line Collision
Avoidance for the Ranger Telerobotic Flight Experiment," was
accepted and will be presented at the 1996 IEEE International Conference on
Robotics and Automation.
<P>

</UL>

<H3> B. Plans for the Next Reporting Period </H3>

<UL>

<LI> Complete integration of the obstacle detection and collision 
avoidance software into the JPL RSI laboratory, and test and evaluate
this software in a real-time environment using the RRC 7-DOF arms.
<P>

<LI> Begin to code and test the graphical animation for optimal 
base placement of Ranger.
<P>

<LI> Support SSL with upgraded models etc., as needed.

</UL>

<H3> C. Schedule </H3>

<IMG SRC="ranger_sch.gif">

<H3>D. Concerns/Issues </H3>

<UL>

<LI> Integration of the obstacle detection and collision
avoidance software by SSL into the Ranger on-board Data Management System
is now scheduled for July, just two months prior to task
termination in September.  JPL is concerned that any slippage
of this schedule by SSL may jeopardize integration of the JPL-developed
software, with a consequent risk that the technology may never
be tested in either the Ranger NBV or the Ranger TFX.

</UL>


<P>
