<a name="rsitt">


<H2> RSI Technology Transfer </H2>

The objective of this task is to make the JPL-developed RSI system available 
at JSC ARMSS (Automated Robotic Maintenance of Space Station) testbed for 
on-site test and technology demonstration of remote surface inspection 
capabilities to the Space Station Program.  JPL will make, test, and deliver 
a copy of the MCS (Manipulator Control System)/TIPSS (Telerobotic Inspection 
Sub-System) system (with some enhancements) to JSC by October 31, 1996.
JSC will procure necessary hardware for the delivery of the TIPSS/MCS system.
JPL will support JSC for installation, evaluation, and demonstration of 
the system delivered.  JPL will loan the JPL sensor head and associated 
sensor electronics to JSC during the JSC test/demo period.

<P>

<H3> A. Significant Activities and Events During this Period </H3>

<UL>

<LI> Completed task plan and workforce staffing.

<LI> Made an agreement with JSC on the loan period of the JPL sensor head 
and its associated electronics.  JSC will return them by January 15, 1997.
The MCS/TIPSS system delivered will stay at JSC.

<LI> JPL compiled the list of hardware procurement items necessary for
JSC delivery of the TIPSS/MCS system.  JSC completed hardware procurement
orders according to the compiled list.

</UL>


<H3> B. Plans for the Next Reporting Period </H3>

<UL> 

<LI> Evaluate automated inspection software. Interactive command scripts
and equivalent C codes for ambient light compensation, reference/comparison 
image differencing, and registration algorithms are being generated to 
examine intermediate images for the evaluation of robustness with respect
to varying ambient sunlight and mis-registration conditions.

<LI> Enhance electronics/hardware including computer-controlled electronic 
shuttering.

<LI> Install/enhance/reconfigure TIPSS and MCS.

</UL>

<H3> C. Schedule </H3>

<IMG SRC="si_schedule.gif">

