<a name="vtgg">

<H2> Vision and Touch Guided Grasping (MIT) </H2>

<H3>Rocky7 Project Quarterly Report for 17 Apr 96</H3><p>

Current JPL Contract: February 16, 1996 - February 15, 1997<p>

During the first quarter of this year's contract our effort has focused on the
elements of Task 6 as detailed below.  The Rocky7 test bed is expected to
become sufficiently operational this summer that we will be able to begin
grasping experiments with it.<p>


Progress made in each item this quarter is listed under that item.<p>
<H3>Statement of Work</H3><p>
Task 6: Simulated Science Experiments<p>
<OL>
<LI>Fabricate laboratory prototype of Rocky7 manipulator and vision systems,
including control and processing electronics, using JPL provided design
information.
<UL>
<LI>Base
  <UL>
  <LI>Have fabricated a simple 2dof base on which to mount the arm and cameras. 
It has two driven wheels, and two caster wheels.  This gives us the extra dof
needed for grasping since our arm is only 1dof.  
  </UL>
<LI>Arm
  <UL>
  <LI>Currently fabricating a 1dof arm which is kinematically similar to the
JPL Version except that it lacks the first axis of rotation.  This joint was
seen to add unfavorable complexity to the arm, without adding significant
additional capability.  
  </UL>
<LI>Hand
  <UL>
  <LI>Currently fabricating a  2dof hand  which is kinematically similar to the
JPL Version except that it does not have infinite rotation.  This capability is
difficult to achieve on the reduced budget, and again it was seen as
unnecessary for the proposed research.  The hand has been made so that the
fingers can easily be changed in order to be able to do both grasping and
digging experiments.
  <LI>Two sets of fingers have been machined for the hand.  One set consists of
flat plates with force sensors mounted on them.  These are being used to carry
out simple grasping experiments, and to validate predictions of the object
graspability model.  The second set of fingers is a scoop design for digging.
</UL>
<LI>Vision System
<UL>
<LI>Two Supercircuits pcb-mount cameras have been purchased, not yet mounted.
<LI>Due to the budget it was necessary to buy a PCI-based frame grabber.
Currently planning to do the vision processing on the PC.
<LI>The vision software is being developed in an incremental approach.  As a
first step, we have implemented a simple blob detector similar to the system
used with the WAM.  This will provide the object COA so that grasping
experiments can begin.
</UL>


</UL>
<LI>Implement and evaluate sample acquisition techniques with this manipulator
including grasping and digging.
<UL>
<LI>NA
</UL>
<LI>Demonstrate in simulated planetary scenario acquisition of indicated
object, presentation to camera for viewing and delivery to sample container.
<UL>
<LI>NA
</UL>
</OL>

<P>
