<a name="rdac">

<H2>Ranger Dexterous Arm Control </H2>

The goal of this task is to augment the operational capabilities of the
dexterous arms in the Ranger Flight Experiment.  These new capabilities will
be developed within the framework of Configuration Control, which has been
developed at JPL and selected for implementation on the Ranger arms.
The FY'95 focus was to develop and implement collision detection and
avoidance capabilities for the Ranger arms, and to transfer the software
to the Ranger project.  The FY'96 focus is to develop, simulate and transfer
the automated base placement capability for the Ranger, and to conduct 
experiments to validate the collision detection/avoidance and base
placement capabilities.
<p>

<IMG SRC="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/people/hayati/Quarterly_Reports/ranger.gif">

<H3> A. Activities in This Reporting Period </H3>
<UL>

<LI> Completed porting, test and validation of the obstacle 
detection and collision avoidance (OD/CA) software in the 
JPL RSI laboratory.
<P>

<LI> Developed and tested several case studies demonstrating
inter-arm, arm-to-object, and self collision avoidance
capabilities using the RRC arms in the JPL RSI laboratory.
<P>

<LI> Presented a paper entitled "On-Line Collision
Avoidance for the Ranger Telerobotic Flight Experiment" 
at the 1996 IEEE International Conference on
Robotics and Automation, Minneapolis.
<P>

<LI> Presented a paper entitled "Obstacle Detection for the Ranger 
Telerobotic Flight Experiment" 
at the International Symposium on
Robotics and Manufacturing (ISRAM), Montpellier, France.

</UL>

<H3> B. Plans for the Next Reporting Period </H3>

<UL>

<LI> Conduct RSI laboratory testing of the effect of slower
obstacle detection updates on collision avoidance performance.
<P>

<LI> Reintegrate the OD/CA software into the Ranger
graphical simulation environment, and package the software
for delivery to the Space Systems Laboratory (SSL) at
the University of Maryland.
<P>

<LI> Code and test software to support optimal
base placement for Ranger.
<P>

<LI> Prepare final report documentation and a videotape
for the close-out of the task.

</UL>

<H3> C. Schedule </H3>

<IMG SRC="ranger_sch.gif">

<H3>D. Concerns/Issues </H3>

<UL>

<LI> SSL has not yet integrated the 7/95-delivered JPL
obstacle detection and collision
avoidance software into the Ranger on-board computer System.
JPL is concerned that this technology may never
be tested in either the Ranger NBV or the Ranger TFX.

</UL>


<P>
