<a name="rsitt">


<H2> RSI Technology Transfer </H2>

The objective of this task is to make the JPL-developed RSI system available 
at JSC ARMSS (Automated Robotic Maintenance of Space Station) testbed for 
on-site test and technology demonstration of remote surface inspection 
capabilities to the Space Station Program.  JPL will make, test, and deliver 
a copy of the MCS (Manipulator Control System)/TIPSS (Telerobotic Inspection 
Sub-System) system (with some enhancements) to JSC by October 31, 1996.
JSC will procure necessary hardware for the delivery of the TIPSS/MCS system.
JPL will support JSC for installation, evaluation, and demonstration of 
the system delivered.  JPL will loan the JPL sensor head and associated 
sensor electronics to JSC during the JSC test/demo period.

<P>

<H3> A. Significant Activities and Events During this Period </H3>

<UL>

<LI> Received all the hardware JSC procured.

<LI> Started MCS and TIPSS installation, and also writing test plans.

<LI> Evaluated automated inspection software of the current RSI system. 

<UL>
<LI> Generated command scripts and equivalent C codes for ambient light 
     compensation and registration algorithms to evaluate robustness with 
     respect to varying ambient sunlight and mis-registration conditions.

<LI> Linearity experiment with different levels of light intensity indicates 
     that the linearization lookup table used in the current ambient light 
     compensation software is good.

<LI> Current Datacube implementation of the image registration algorithm
     tends to generate false flaws in high contrast areas. Identified 
     source of the problem, and it is currently being fixed.
</UL>

<LI> Implemented "computer-controlled" electronic shuttering synchronized with
     strobe lighting. 

<UL>
<LI> Image inspections with 8 ms (1/2 exposure), 4 ms (1/4 exposure), and 
     1 ms (1/16 exposure) shuttering are tested successfully. 

<LI> Electronic shuttering reduces the camera reception of the ambient 
     sunlight while keeping the same camera reception of the strobe lighting.
</UL>

</UL>


<H3> B. Plans for the Next Reporting Period </H3>

<UL> 

<LI> Install/enhance/reconfigure TIPSS and MCS.

<LI> Complete the automated inspection software evaluation after the
     Datacube implementation fix.

<LI> Generate test plans, perform experiments, and produce documents

</UL>

