<TITLE> Lavic Lake Desert Test Self Inspection</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#8f8fff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00ff00" VLINK="#0000ff">

<h1>Rover Self Inspection</h1>

During its long traverse across Mars, a rover will need to be periodically
inspected.  High wheel currents, or lack of vehicle motion may imply 
a stuck wheel or vehicle high-centering, which must be accessed by ground
controllers.  Also, a visual record of vehicle wear over time during the
traverse will help in planning the remainder of mission, as well future
vehicle and mission design.<p>

<hr>
<h3>Typical Inspection Positions</h3>
<a  href="images/r7inspectSide.jpg">
<img src="images/r7inspectSide_medium.jpg"></a>
<a  href="images/r7inspectFront.jpg">
<img src="images/r7inspectFront_medium.jpg"></a><p>

<hr>
<h3>Typical Inspection Images</h3>
<a  href="images/tandem/right.gif">
<img src="images/tandem/right_medium.gif"></a>
<a  href="images/steering/left.gif">
<img src="images/steering/left_medium.gif"></a>

<hr>
<p>
Maintained by:
<a href="/people/volpe/homepage.html">Richard Volpe</a><br>
Last updated 7 January 1997
