<title> 
Rover Multispectral Imaging
</title>

<h1> 
Rover Multispectral Imaging <br>
</h1>
<hr>

<h3>
MAST CAMERAS<p>
</h3>

Red, green, and blue filter images from the mast, and the
combined color result.<p>
<img src="images/mast_clockR.gif">
<img src="images/mast_clockG.gif">
<img src="images/mast_clockB.gif">
<a href="images/mast_clock.tif"><img src="images/mast_clock.jpg"></a>
<p>

The filters are from <a href="http://www.rolyn.com/rothinf3.htm">
Rolyn Optics Company</a>. Red has a cutoff below about 600 nm,
blue above 480 nm, and green bandpass between 500-580 nm.
<p>

<hr>
<p>
<h3>
CLOSE-UP IMAGER<p>
</h3>
Red, green, and blue illumination images from the close-up imager, 
and the combined color result.<p>
<img src="images/cui_cartoonR.gif">
<img src="images/cui_cartoonG.gif">
<img src="images/cui_cartoonB.gif">
 <a href="images/cui_cartoon.tif"><img src="images/cui_cartoon.jpg"></a>
<p>

Unlike the mast imagery, the close-up imager attempts to obtain color
by illumination.  The RGB illuminating LEDs are at 700, 565, 466 nm.
Other LEDs at 590, 630, 880, 940 nm are also integrated into the
system.  Calibration compensation for uneven illumination is currently
being investigated.
<p>


<hr>

<p>




</DOC>
