<TITLE> Lavic Lake Test Panoramic Imaging</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#8f8fff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00ff00" VLINK="#0000ff">

<h1>Mast Stereo Panoramic Imaging</h1>

Without the aid of a lander nearby, a long range rover must be able
to image the surrounding terrain from a relatively high vantage point.
This imagery is used for path planning, terrain feature tracking for localization,
and selection of science targets. Only monocular views are shown here.

<hr>
