<TITLE> Ground Control Station Task </TITLE>

<H1>Ground Control Station Task
<p> 
<a href="images/gcsComp.gif"><IMG SRC="images/gcsComp.small.50.gif"></a>
<BR>

<H3>

The Ground Control Station is a system which allows an operator
to interactively build, simulate and execution task sequences.
The interface provides the ground control station functionality
of a ground-remote telerobot control system.  
Time delay between the ground control station and the space-based
robot control system prevent the use of control modes which
require closed loop control between the local and remote sites.
All ground control commands are executed autonomously at the remote site.
<P>

There may be applications, such as for Space Station, where there will
also be a remote operator control station.
In such a system, the ground or the remote control stations could control
the robotic system or work together.  
For example, the ground station could generate task sequences and 
telemeter them to the remote control station from which they could be executed.
The remote control station might also use direct teleoperation since time
delay may not be a significant factor.
<P>
 
The operator develops commands at the local site by selecting command types
and providing specific data to the commands and providing logic
around the commands.
The operator will interact with the system in multiple ways.
The operator can command the system via menu interaction,
voice input or in a graphical environment where desired commands
are implied by the operator's actions.
<P>

<H4>
Current Task Members:
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="/people/hayati/homepage.html">Samad Hayati (Task Manager)</A><LI> <A HREF="/people/backes/homepage.html">Paul Backes (Cognizant Engineer)</A>
<LI> Antal Bejczy</A>
<LI> <A HREF="/people/bon/homepage.html">Bruce Bon</A>
<LI> <A HREF="/people/tharp/homepage.html">Gregory Tharp</A>
</UL>

</H4>

</DOC>
