<TITLE>DARTS: Dynamics Algorithms for Real-Time Simulation</TITLE>
 <P>
<STRONG>DARTS</STRONG> is a spacecraft dynamics
simulation package for real-time, hardware-in-the-loop simulations for
testing and verification of flight software and hardware. It runs on
embedded processors, special purpose vector-processing boards and can
also be used in work-station for off-line dynamics simulations for the
design and evaluation of control algorithms and software. Currently the
<STRONG>DARTS</STRONG> package is in use by the <A
HREF="http://tsunami.jpl.nasa.gov/~leem/rto-home/rto_home.html">Cassini</A> project and by the <A
HREF="http://atlas2/fst/home.html">Flight System Testbed</A>. On completion, the new
version of <STRONG>DARTS</STRONG> will be used by the <A
HREF="http:http://mpfwww/">Mars Pathfinder</A> and the <A
HREF="http://olivaw.jpl.nasa.gov/gll/phk/galileo_project.html">Galileo</A> projects as well.

<STRONG>DARTS</STRONG> can simulate the dynamics of
tree-topology, flexible multibody systems such as spacecraft, robots,
vehicles, molecular systems etc. <STRONG>DARTS</STRONG>
makes use of algorithms developed using the <A
HREF="~jain/www/soa.html">spatial operator algebra</A> framework for
multibody system dynamics. The <STRONG>DARTS</STRONG> S/C dynamics computational
engine has been integrated into the <A HREF="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/tasks/dshell">Dshell</A> spacecraft simulation environment.

<P>
Current Task Members:
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="http://robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/people/jain/homepage.html">Abhinandan Jain</A>
<LI> Hari Das
<LI> Dave Rathbun
</UL>

Contributors:
<UL>
<LI> Guy Man (<A HREF="//robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/people/jain/computational-controls.html">Computational Controls</A>)
<LI> Guillermo Rodriguez (<A HREF="//robotics.jpl.nasa.gov/people/jain/soa.html">Spatial Operator Algebra</A>)
<LI> Amir Fijany (<A HREF="http://tsunami.jpl.nasa.gov/~leem/rto-home/rto_home.html">Cassini</A>)
<LI> Jimmy Roberts (<A HREF="http://tsunami.jpl.nasa.gov/~leem/rto-home/rto_home.html">Cassini</A>)
</UL>

</UL>

