<Title> JPL HAZBOT III - Technical Specifications </Title>

<H1><IMG SRC="/home/welch/HAZBOT93/images/hazbot3.gif"> HAZBOT III </H1>
<H2> Emergency Response Robotics Project </H2>

<H2>Technical Data </H2>

<HR>

<H4>6 DOF MANIPULATOR</H4>
<UL>
<LI> Smooth profile to reduce possible snagging and ease decontamination
<LI> Sealing and internal channels to support pressurization
<LI>  Low backlash through use of harmonic drives
<LI>  Internally mounted brushless DC motors
<LI>  Ross-Hime 3 DOF Omni-Wrist
<LI>  40 lb payload capacity (at 5 ft reach)
<LI>  30 lb grip force
<LI>  Wrist mounted camera
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>COLOR CAMERA</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  8:1 zoom
<LI>  Autofocus and autoiris
<LI>  Pan/tilt platform on movable boom (provisions for second platform)
<LI>  Microphone (speaker on main chassis)
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>TRACK DRIVE</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  From REMOTEC ANDROS Mark V-A robotic vehicle
<LI>  Articulated front and rear tracks allow traversal of rough terrain
<LI>  Lugged tracks enable stair climbing
<LI>  Internally mounted Brushless DC motors
<LI>  Internal channels and sealing to support pressurization
<LI>  Top speed ~0.7mph
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>ON-BOARD BATTERIES</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  Batteries (24V) provide power for all on-board systems
<LI>  Average mission life ~3 hours
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>COMMUNICATION TETHER</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  100m tether provides 2-way communication to operator (video, audio, & data)
<LI>  Optional trickle charge of batteries over tether to extend mission life
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>CHEMICAL SENSOR</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  AIM USA 3300 chemical gas detector
<LI>  Sensors for OX, CO, as well as a general combustible gas sensor
<LI>  Integrated into manipulator
<LI>  Draws samples in through gripper tip
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>PRESSURIZATION SYSTEM</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  On-board pressure tanks allows pressurization of system for operation in atmospheres containing combustible gases 
<LI>  Pressurization monitored by on-board pressure sensors
<LI>  All solid state electronics and brushless DC motors (non-arching components) are used as an additional precaution should the pressurization system fail
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>OTHER</H4>
<UL>
<LI>  Weight approximately 600lbs
<LI>  Size in stowed position approximately 28" wide, 42" long, and 40" tall
<LI>  On-board winch system
<LI>  68030 VME based on-board computer
</UL>

<HR>

<H4>
For Further Information Contact: <A href="/home/welch/www/homepage.html">Rick Welch</A> <BR>
</H4>
